title: For Sale:  USED SKD PIG PLATE CARRIER + AR500 AND KEVLAR ARMOR SET
location: San Jose, Almaden, San Francisco, California
postcontent:
I am selling my khaki tan SKD PIG plate carrier, along with all armor peripherals with it. I am selling it because I need the cash for other purchases. This carrier has been one of my favorites so far- it comes with two internal kangaroo-style magazine pouches that fit AK mags perfectly (and will securely hold AR mags with a bungee-system peripheral sold by SKD), and the plate pockets are designed to take up to 11x14 XL plates and soft armor, however 10x12 plates work just fine due to an inner Velcro lining that holds the plates in place. This carrier is very high quality, comfortable even while weighed down, not likely to make you overheat while wearing and I've been mostly impressed by it and I'll probably regret to see it gone, but I could use the cash.

What I'm selling with the carrier, if interested, is a curved 10x12 level III AR500 plate, a flat 10x12 level III AR500 plate, two 6x8 curved side plates with the anti-spalling coating buildup, two 10x12 plate backers designed to lessen impact trauma, two 6x8 side plate backers designed to lessen impact trauma, 2 side plate carriers, 2 original 11x14 plate backers, and finally 2 11x14 level IIIA Kevlar plate backers to defeat frag, pistol bullets that skim the plate, or armor-piercing rifle rounds that might pass through the hard plates, which is currently installed instead of the foam.

This carrier is not designed for smaller statured people, as I have it cinched down about as much as it can go to have it accommodate me, being 5' 11" and 180 lbs. if you're a larger guy, or if you like the peace of mind of being able to accept XL plates, you'll appreciate this carrier more than a Banshee or most Condor carriers. It is very well made and so far the only thing to have needed mending in the year or so that I've had it is the right kangaroo pouch, which came apart at the seam. It was easily fixed with a little sewing and is now secure.

Doing the math, I've found that I spent just over a grand on all this armor, not counting the shipping costs, AND the 8~ weeks that AR500.com took to manufacture my armor plates. If you choose to buy this, you'd have to pay one shipping cost (or none, if you pick up locally) and you don't have to wait to get your plates made.

Here's the math:
1x SKD PIG carrier- 329.00
2x PIG side plate carriers- 29.50
1x AR500 10x12 level III curved plate w/ trauma backer- 120.00
1x AR500 10x12 level III flat plate w/ trauma backer- 100.00
2x Ar500 6x8 level III curved side plates w/ paxcon buildup and trauma backers- 146.00
2x Armour-Wear.com 11x14 level IIIA soft kevlar panels- 299.90

TOTAL: 1024.40 NOT COUNTING SHIPPING


I'd be willing to part with the entire package for 700 if you pick it up, or 750 if you want it shipped, on top of you covering the shipping costs.

I could also only sell certain parts of it, or sell it without certain parts, if the right deal is made. I'd be more than willing to hear you out if you want certain components, and I could even be persuaded to make a trade if you have something I especially want. I'd also be willing to sell for under what I paid for them, but not too far under.

Also, body armor is illegal for felons or use in crimes. I will not sell to you if you are underage, are a non-resident, are badly dressed, or have teardrop/gang tattoos. Bring your ID. I will NOT respond to messages or emails that look like they were written by a high school dropout. If you wish to trade a gun for it, FFL transfer is REQUIRED and it must be legal to own in California. If we sell locally, we will meet in the daytime outside of a supermarket, police station, gun store, or any other place where you'd have to be a complete moron to make trouble. When in person, you can examine the armor as much as you'd like, and if you want an image of a specific piece or more detail, message me and I'll take a picture for you. Don't waste my time and I won't waste yours. Thank you.

title: For Sale:  USED BULLETSAFE LEVEL IIIA BULLETPROOF VEST, MEDIUM
location: San Jose, Almaden, San Francisco, California
postcontent:
Up for sale is my Bulletsafe vest, medium-size, level IIIA. I'm selling to get cash for other purchases.  This is a heavy-duty IIIA vest made to stop .44 magnum rounds. It's thick and hard enough to even stop hard stabbings, and has pockets to accept 10x12 trauma plates on both the front and back. However, it is not the most concealable vest- under a shirt it's about as obvious as it gets; to conceal it you'd have to wear at least a heavy coat or a down vest. For a vest to throw on during a home invasion, it's alright, however it's not the most tactical thing in the world. If you're on a budget though, this will do you just fine.

I got the vest from Bulletsafe.com for 300 dollars, however, I'd be willing to do a face-to-face sale for 190 even, and 225 to have it shipped. I'd even be able to entertain and cough up cash for certain trades, if you happen to have something I want.

Also, if you'd be interested in buying 10x12 plates with this, I am also selling AR500 plates and I could throw one or two of them in with the vest if you wanted to cut a deal. If you're after something more tactical with magazine pouches and dedicated rifle protection, I am also selling an SKD plate carrier here: http://www.armslist.com/posts/4831070/san-francisco-california-tactical-gear-for-sale--used-skd-pig-plate-carrier---armor-set

finally, body armor is illegal for felons or use in crimes. I will not sell to you if you are underage, are a non-resident, are badly dressed, or have teardrop/gang tattoos. Bring your ID. I will NOT respond to messages or emails that look like they were written by a high school dropout. If you wish to trade a gun for it, FFL transfer is REQUIRED and it must be legal to own in California. If we sell locally, we will meet in the daytime outside of a supermarket, police station, gun store, or any other place where you'd have to be a complete moron to make trouble. When in person, you can examine the armor as much as you'd like, and if you want an image of a specific piece or more detail, message me and I'll take a picture for you. Don't waste my time and I won't waste yours. Thank you.

title: For Sale:  Safety for oil and gas employees
postcontent:
Oil, gas and petrochemical industry is in lot of risk as they deal with highly inflammable materials.  This is the reason why the employees and workers of this industry should be safeguarded from any kind of accidents or untoward incidents. These industries should get certified in ISO 29001 which lays down standards regarding how to keep the work place safe for the employees and workers, how to keep accidents at bay and what measures can be taken to make sure that no accidents take place at the work place. title: For Sale:  Remington 700 SA Detachable Mag Black Synthetic Stock
location: Clayton, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
I have a factory Remington short action stock for sell.  I was going to bed my action into this stock but ended up getting another stock because I like a little wider forend than this stock has.  This stock is really ridged for a factory stock, much more study that what I've seen on Savage or Marlin rifles so I think a bed job in this stock would make for a pretty accurate rifle.  I have already done some inletting of the stock in preparation for a bedding job so it really needs to be bedded to your action to get good accuracy.  I have recently done a bedding job on my hunting rifle and my average group size went from around 1.5MOA to around 0.625MOA after bedding the action to the stock.

Note that this stock is inletted for bottom metal that uses the Remington box magazines.  It may work with the hinged floor plate type bottom metal but I haven't tried, looks like the only difference is it has recesses for the box mag release tabs that wouldn't be needed with the hinged type bottom metal.

I'm asking $35 for the stock and I may would entertain the ideal of bedding your barreled action to this stock for an extra $50 if interested but I typically don't work on other people firearms.
